This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of convolutional neural networks (CNN) for image-based tasks, such as classification and regression. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of data augmentation for domain transfer tasks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of style transfer techniques, which could potentially place it in sub-categories such as cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
